# Translation Rule for Blog Articles
Type: Workspace Rule
Description: Translation guidelines for blog articles in markdown format, ensuring consistency between English (US) and Spanish (ES) versions while allowing flexible translation coverage.

**Purpose:**
This rule ensures consistency in multilingual blog content while maintaining a youthful tone and preserving technical accuracy. Unlike the main website repo, translations are optional and managed through an external content platform.

---

## 1. File Structure

### Naming Convention
- **English Articles:** `[article-name].us.md` or `[article-name].md`
- **Spanish Articles:** `[article-name].es.md`
- **Translation Pairs:** Use identical base name with different language suffixes
  - ✅ `full-stack-developer.md` + `full-stack-developer.es.md`
  - ✅ `coding-bootcamp.us.md` + `coding-bootcamp.es.md`

### File Location
- **All blog articles:** `/blog/` directory
- **No subdirectories** for language separation

### Translation Approach
- **Optional Translations:** Not every article requires translation (unlike main repo)
- **Standalone Articles:** Articles can exist in a single language when:
  - Content is region-specific (e.g., Miami-only content)
  - Content is time-sensitive and translation isn't immediately needed
  - Content targets a specific language audience
- **No Workflow Statuses:** All articles must use `status: "published"` (workflow statuses are deprecated)

## 2. Frontmatter Metadata Requirements

### Required Fields
All articles must include YAML frontmatter with these required fields:

```yaml
---
author: "4Geeks Academy"  # Or use authors: ["username1", "username2"] as array
cluster: "relevant-cluster"  # Language-specific cluster (see mapping below)
excerpt: "Max 160 characters including spaces"
tags: ["tag1", "tag2", "tag3"]  # Array of relevant keywords
template: "landing_post"  # Always use this template
title: "SEO-optimized title (5-10 words)"
status: "published"  # Always "published" (workflow statuses deprecated)
date: "2025-01-27T10:30:00+00:00"  # ISO 8601 format, must be valid
target_seo_keyword: "main-keyword"  # Optional but recommended
cover: "https://api.example.com/images/cover.jpg"  # Optional: Image URL from API
---
```

### Status Values
**Always use:** `status: "published"`

**Note:** Status workflow functionality is deprecated in this older repo. All articles must have `status: "published"` regardless of translation state or draft status.

### Cover Images
- **`cover`**: Use for **image URLs from API** (always URLs, never local paths)
- **Note:** `cover_local` is deprecated - all images now come from the API as URLs

### Authors Field
- If using `authors`, must be an array: `authors: ["username1", "username2"]`
- Single author can use: `author: "4Geeks Academy"`

## 3. Content Translation Guidelines

### Metadata Translation Requirements

**Must Translate:**
- `title`: Full translation maintaining SEO keywords (max 60 chars)
- `excerpt`: Complete translation within 160 character limit (strict)
- `cluster`: Use language-appropriate cluster (see mapping below)
- `tags`: Translate tags to target language

**Keep Unchanged:**
- `author` or `authors`: Same value across languages
- `template`: Always "landing_post"
- `date`: Same publication date
- `target_seo_keyword`: May adapt for language-specific SEO

### Language Style
- **Tone:** Informal and direct
  - ✅ Spanish: Use "tú" form (e.g., "Aprende a programar")
  - ❌ Spanish: Avoid "usted" form (e.g., "Aprenda a programar")
- **Target Audience:** 18-25 year olds
- **Technical Terms:** Keep consistent
  - "bootcamp", "JavaScript", "Python" remain unchanged
  - "Full Stack Developer" can remain or translate to "Desarrollador Full Stack"

### Cluster Mapping (Language-Specific)

| English Cluster | Spanish Equivalent |
|----------------|-------------------|
| `ai-powered-learning` | `aprendizaje-potenciado-con-ia` |
| `career-growth` | `crecimiento-profesional` |
| `coding-bootcamp` | `bootcamp-de-programacion` |
| `learn-python` | `aprender-a-programar` |
| `full-stack-developer` | `desarrollador-full-stack` |
| `software-engineer` | N/A (keep in English) |
| `trends-and-tech` | N/A (keep in English) |

### Markdown Content Translation
- **Structure Preservation:** Maintain heading hierarchy (H2, H3, etc.)
- **Links:** Update internal links to language-specific versions when available
  - English: `[link text](/us/page)` or `[link text](https://4geeksacademy.com/us/page)`
  - Spanish: `[link text](/es/pagina)` or `[link text](https://4geeksacademy.com/es/pagina)`
- **Images:** Keep same image paths; translate alt text to target language
- **Code Blocks:** Keep code unchanged; translate only comments
- **Lists & Tables:** Translate all content while preserving formatting

## 4. Quality Control Process

### Pre-commit Checklist

**Frontmatter Validation:**
- [ ] All required fields present (title, date, status, excerpt, cluster, tags)
- [ ] Excerpt within 160 character limit (strict)
- [ ] Cluster matches language (EN/ES clusters from mapping)
- [ ] Tags translated appropriately
- [ ] Date format correct: `YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS+00:00` (ISO 8601)
- [ ] Status is `"published"` (required - workflow statuses deprecated)
- [ ] Authors field is array if used (not string)

**Cover Images (Optional):**
- [ ] `cover` uses API URL only (e.g., `https://api.example.com/images/...`)
- [ ] Never use local paths or `../` in cover field
- [ ] `cover_local` is deprecated - don't use

**Content Quality:**
- [ ] Headings maintain hierarchy
- [ ] Internal links updated for language
- [ ] Code blocks preserved correctly
- [ ] Technical terms handled consistently
- [ ] Tone matches target audience (informal, "tú" form for ES)

**Translation Pairs (when creating pairs):**
- [ ] Base filename identical except language suffix
- [ ] Both files in `/blog/` directory
- [ ] Content semantically equivalent
- [ ] Language-specific clusters and tags used

### Platform Validation

**External platform automatically validates:**
- ✅ Title exists (required)
- ✅ Date is valid (moment.js validation)
- ✅ Status is "published" (required)
- ✅ Authors is an array (if used)
- ✅ Cover images use correct URL format (if used)
- ✅ No duplicate slugs across articles

**Note:** No local testing required - validation runs when content syncs to platform.

## 5. Translation Workflow

### When to Translate (Priority)
**Create translation pairs for:**
- High-traffic articles (check analytics)
- Evergreen content (bootcamp guides, career advice)
- SEO-critical pages
- Content targeting both EN/ES markets

**Can defer translation for:**
- Time-sensitive announcements
- Location-specific content (single market)
- Partnership announcements (region-specific)
- Experimental/test content

### Translation Process

**Step 1: Create/Publish English article**
```yaml
# full-stack-developer.us.md
---
title: "What Is A Full Stack Developer?"
status: "published"  # Always published
cluster: "full-stack-developer"
excerpt: "Learn what a Full Stack Developer is and how to become one."
tags: ["full-stack", "career-growth", "web-development"]
date: "2025-01-15T10:00:00+00:00"
template: "landing_post"
---
```

**Step 2: Create Spanish translation**
```yaml
# full-stack-developer.es.md (new file)
---
title: "¿Qué Es Un Desarrollador Full Stack?"
status: "published"  # Always published
cluster: "desarrollador-full-stack"  # Language-specific cluster
excerpt: "Conoce qué es un desarrollador full-stack y cómo convertirte en uno."
tags: ["full-stack", "crecimiento-profesional", "desarrollo-web"]
date: "2025-01-15T10:00:00+00:00"  # Same date as English version
template: "landing_post"
---
```

**Note:** There is no draft or pending status - both files are always `status: "published"`

